.TH "WLCF" "1" "May 06, 2026" "" "WLCF"
.SH NAME
wlcf \- WLCF 1.0.0
.SH OVERVIEW
.SS wlcf: Weak Lensing Correlation Function
.sp
\fBAuthors:\fP A. Aviles, J.C. Hidalgo, E.A. Moreno\-Alcala, G. Niz, S. Ramirez, Mario A. Rodriguez\-Meza, S. Samario\-Nava
.sp
For download and information, see \X'tty: link https://github.com/rodriguezmeza/wlcf.git'\fI\%https://github.com/rodriguezmeza/wlcf.git\fP\X'tty: link' .
.SS Introduction
.sp
\fBwlcf\fP is a C code designed to compute cosmological correlation functions using theoretical frameworks such as Standard Perturbation Theory (SPT), Effective Field Theory (EFT), and the Halo Model. Currently, it focuses on the computation of the \fBthree\-point correlation function (3PCF)\fP for galaxy weak lensing convergence in a plane\-wave expansion.
Paper available at (\X'tty: link https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.16847'\fI\%https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.16847\fP\X'tty: link').
.SS Compiling and getting started
.sp
Download the code by cloning it from:
\X'tty: link https://github.com/rodriguezmeza/wlcf.git'\fI\%https://github.com/rodriguezmeza/wlcf.git\fP\X'tty: link' .
.sp
\fBDependencies:\fP
\fIwlcf\fP optionally requires \fBGSL (GNU Scientific Library)\fP and \fBFFTW3\fP installed in your system. Make sure to adapt the paths to these libraries in \fIMakefile_machine\fP\&.
.sp
Tu run the code go to the \fIwlcf\fP directory and compile the code:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
$ cd wlcf
$ make clean
$ make all
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
The code has been tested with modern versions of \fIgcc\fP\&. OpenMP support is optional but recommended for parallel execution. In addition, the code provides a Python wrapper that allows it to be run and controlled directly from Python.
.sp
To verify that the code runs correctly:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
$ cd tests
$ ./wlcf
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
This will execute the code using default parameters. A directory named \fIOutput\fP will be created inside \fItests\fP, where all results are stored, including:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
output data files (e.g., \fIzetam*\fP, \fIBmells*\fP, \fIBnk*\fP)
.IP \(bu 2
a log file inside \fIOutput/tmp\fP
.UNINDENT
.sp
You can consult man page:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
$ man ../docs/wlcf.1
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
or open with a browser the html file: docs/man/wlcf.html
