.SH 3-POINT CORRELATION FUNCTIONS
.sp
\fBwlcf\fP computes \fBthree\-point correlation functions (3PCF)\fP for scalar fields, such as the weak lensing convergence \ekappa\&. These higher\-order statistics provide access to non\-Gaussian information in the large\-scale structure of the Universe.
.sp
In particular, the code evaluates the correlation:
.sp
.ce
\elangle \ekappa(\ehat{n}_1),\ekappa(\ehat{n}_2),\ekappa(\ehat{n}_3) \erangle
.ce 0
.sp
using a plane\-wave expansion and a harmonic decomposition.
.sp
\fBHarmonic base\fP
.sp
The angular dependence of the 3PCF is expressed in a \fBharmonic basis\fP, where the signal is decomposed into multipoles. This allows for an efficient and structured representation of the correlation function.
.sp
The expansion is performed in terms of angular modes labeled by an index m, leading to a set of coefficients:
.sp
.ce
\ezeta_m(\etheta_1, \etheta_2)
.ce 0
.sp
where:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\etheta_1, \etheta_2 are angular separations
.IP \(bu 2
m = 0, 1, \edots, m_{\emathrm{max}} is the multipole index
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBOutput\fP
.sp
The results of the harmonic decomposition are stored in files:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
zetam0.txt
zetam1.txt
\&...
zetamN.txt
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
along with the corresponding angular grid:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
theta_array.txt
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
These outputs can be used to reconstruct or visualize the full three\-point correlation function.
